Two days ago, on 29/04 at 3:20 PM, I saw a new doctor at the RBWH
STARS clinic regarding the management of MDA5+ DM and described my
recurrent, strange symptoms. I told the doctor I'm able and happy to
read a study, but aware I don't have a broad view so I either bring
them anything unusual to parse, or I leave it all alone, basically if
it wasn't happening 6 months ago I bring it to them. Dr then went and
consulted with Dr Kubler.

Dr Kubler then invited my wife and I into his office. During this
meeting we discussed many different things, Dr Kubler seemed to be
proposing or considering several contradictory ideas. The principal
ones I remember were:

- He characterised my MDA5+ DM as skin only, no muscle involvement.
- He said the elevated liver enzymes from Oct, Nov, Dec were probably
muscle breakdown. We didn't highlight this at the time, but obviously
contradicts the above.
- CK at 220 was minor (true) but rose 40% in a month on mostly
full-dose mycophenolate.
- He said the type 1 interferons probably contributed to leg plaque
deposition as they do with lupus.
- He said MDA5+ DM can't explain any mental changes and was probably
just stress from the diagnosis. I told him we didnt have one at the
time and the personality changes and brain fog increased throughout
October, peaking in November until I took prednisone at the end of
November/December. He then said it was probably the stress of
diagnostic uncertainty. I disagreed and told him that sounded like
intellectual laziness to avoid complexity.
- He said the hand pain was psychosomatic, I said it's bilateral and
also active in the thumb. He said both were mechanical. I asked why
that's never happened before - except during the last 6 month period?
Why did Dr Kevin Huang characterise both arms having thickened and
inflamed tendons? Why did the hand therapist agree? He then shifted to
say it was probably diabetes related, then started to imply my control
was bad, even though it wasn't. When contradicted he said, "Well,
having high blood sugars can do this." Again I asked why this never
happened except in the past 6 months? Why did two specialists raise
eosinophilic fasciitis? He said he didn't think it was EF. I said,
"Sure, fine. I don't really care what's causing it, I just want it to
stop." I asked why the eosinophilia kept coming back, he looked at my
bloods and said it was mild. I agreed, but raised it wasnt during Nov
Dec, but went down on the prednisone. This seemed to change his
opinion slightly, he admitted to not knowing and agreed to a biopsy.
He actually said to us "You (pointing at me) didn't want one(a
biopsy)." After the MRI (no contrast) it showed nothing, so he said he
had nothing to biopsy. I didn't correct him at the time, it seemed
minor. He said he doesn't think the biopsy will show anything, maybe
minor muscle changes. I asked why the damage only showed with contrast
which everyone kept telling me doesn't matter. We had a discussion
about gadolinium and magnets in water and leaky cell damage. He again,
could not explain why this only happened during this 6 month period
but still characterised it as psychosomatic. I told him it wasn't. He
said I should "Keep an open mind". Offended, I told him, it never has
been or was, I'm not a child, our son was seriously ill for months at
QCH with invasive group A strep, this isn't the first time I've had
"stress". We left it there.
- He said regardless none of this affects insurance, because that's
cumulative. I said, "Well, that's not really the focus right now."
Half joking, I said I used to be the worlds best Dad and the worlds
most mediocre husband. That's goal one. I said I've been feeling
better, but not well or good, over the past 2 weeks but if it keeps
going I might be able to get back to work at some point. The only
change I can point to is that my low-grade, raised temperature of four
months has gone down. But I'd like to consistently get back to that;
that's the primary goal. Sustaining the physical or cognitive load
while working was the secondary - longer term goal. But for my own
mental health I need to achieve goal 1 first. Wondering why he
diverted us, we then discussed the next steps.

On leaving the appointment the contradictions started to become
clearer. My wife, Bernadette, and I try to watch influencing each
other, we just want to know what's going on and for it to stop. She
mentioned seeing different studies that agree MDA5+ DM can cause
personality shifts. Lupus is known to cause potentially severe
psychiatric effects from type 1 interferons=E2=80=94the same process Dr Fat=
hi
(cardiologist) and Kubler himself admitted may have played a role in
the leg plague. This became more confusing as my heart test score and
fitness were excellent, which I'm very happy with as a baseline!

I reviewed the Go2 health notes in the last 24 hours; I was horrified
by how little they genuinely engaged with me as a patient. However,
once overcoming my initial digust - I was shocked by how closely
Loughrey's and Carroll match the effects of type one interferons.
Depression, chronic fatigue, irritability, psychosis, personality
change. I was aware (I tend to focus on cell and molecular pathways)
that they can affect serotonin and thought that maybe the cognitive
load was unmasking autism and that a lack of serotonin was making me a
jerk. The notes reminded me that the dexamfetamine stopped working in
a matter of weeks during the flare, before I knew what the hell was
going on. I easily slept through 20mg of it.during this time.

On reflection and while writing this my impression is that Dr Kubler
was seeking every excuse to avoid actually having a real conversation
on the issue. The goalposts kept shifting, while he may have been
throwing out differentials, they all contradict other differentials
and the facts and history, to me it seems the most parsimonious
explanation is the type 1 interferon-mediated disease had the known
effects of type 1 interferons. Having read the go2 health notes
properly, the fact he independently raised insurance and that the
doctors saw a sick father seeking help and having seen the effects
professionally of exactly this - doctors circling the wagons, lying,
trusting file notes over people to their detriment it really seemed to
me that Kubler was talking to exactly those notes - not the people
infront of him. My wife and I have discussed this. This note is
somewhere between a file note for the meeting, a diary entry and my
attempt to organise my thoughts; however, I have not been shared with
her at this stage.

